<!-- BASICS -->
<section id="basics">
  <div class="section-label">The Fundamentals</div>
  <h2>Investing <em>101</em></h2>
  <p class="section-intro">Before chasing returns, master the foundations. These core concepts are the building blocks of every successful investor's toolkit.</p>
  <div class="basics-grid">
    <div class="basics-card">
      <div class="card-num">01 — CONCEPT</div>
      <h3>Compound Interest</h3>
      <p>The most powerful force in investing. When your returns generate their own returns, your wealth grows exponentially. Starting early — even with small amounts — matters more than starting big later.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="basics-card">
      <div class="card-num">02 — CONCEPT</div>
      <h3>Diversification</h3>
      <p>Don't put all your eggs in one basket. Spreading investments across asset classes, sectors, and geographies reduces risk without sacrificing long-term returns.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="basics-card">
      <div class="card-num">03 — CONCEPT</div>
      <h3>Risk vs. Reward</h3>
      <p>Higher potential returns almost always come with higher risk. Understanding your personal risk tolerance — and your time horizon — shapes every smart investment decision.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="basics-card">
      <div class="card-num">04 — CONCEPT</div>
      <h3>Asset Classes</h3>
      <p>Stocks, bonds, real estate, commodities, and cash each behave differently in various market conditions. A healthy portfolio uses multiple asset classes strategically.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="basics-card">
      <div class="card-num">05 — CONCEPT</div>
      <h3>Dollar-Cost Averaging</h3>
      <p>Invest a fixed amount regularly regardless of market conditions. This removes emotion from the equation and naturally buys more shares when prices are low.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="basics-card">
      <div class="card-num">06 — CONCEPT</div>
      <h3>Expense Ratios</h3>
      <p>Even small fees compound dramatically over decades. A 1% difference in annual fees can cost tens of thousands over a 30-year investment horizon. Keep costs low.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- STRATEGIES -->
<section id="strategies" class="strategies">
  <div class="section-label">Investment Approaches</div>
  <h2>Proven <em>Strategies</em></h2>
  <p class="section-intro">No single strategy fits everyone. Match your approach to your goals, timeline, and risk tolerance.</p>
  <div class="strat-list">
    <div class="strat-item">
      <div class="strat-name">Index Investing</div>
      <div class="strat-desc">Buy the whole market through low-cost index funds like S&P 500 ETFs. Beats most active managers over the long term due to low fees and broad diversification.</div>
      <div class="strat-badge badge-low">Low Risk</div>
    </div>
    <div class="strat-item">
      <div class="strat-name">Value Investing</div>
      <div class="strat-desc">Find undervalued companies trading below their intrinsic worth. Popularized by Warren Buffett and Benjamin Graham. Requires patience and deep research.</div>
      <div class="strat-badge badge-med">Medium Risk</div>
    </div>
    <div class="strat-item">
      <div class="strat-name">Growth Investing</div>
      <div class="strat-desc">Target companies expected to grow faster than average. Higher potential upside but more volatile. Tech and innovation sectors dominate this approach.</div>
      <div class="strat-badge badge-med">Medium Risk</div>
    </div>
    <div class="strat-item">
      <div class="strat-name">Dividend Investing</div>
      <div class="strat-desc">Build a portfolio of stocks that pay regular dividends. Creates passive income that can be reinvested or used as cash flow. Ideal for wealth preservation.</div>
      <div class="strat-badge badge-low">Low Risk</div>
    </div>
    <div class="strat-item">
      <div class="strat-name">Momentum Trading</div>
      <div class="strat-desc">Buy assets trending upward and sell those trending down. Requires active monitoring and discipline. Often combined with technical analysis signals.</div>
      <div class="strat-badge badge-high">High Risk</div>
    </div>
    <div class="strat-item">
      <div class="strat-name">Real Estate (REITs)</div>
      <div class="strat-desc">Invest in real estate without buying property directly. REITs must distribute 90% of taxable income to shareholders, offering consistent dividends.</div>
      <div class="strat-badge badge-med">Medium Risk</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

