<!-- MARKET EDGE TIPS -->
<section id="edge">
  <div class="tips-header">
    <div>
      <div class="section-label">Competitive Advantage</div>
      <h2>Stay Ahead of the <em>Market</em></h2>
      <p class="section-intro" style="margin-bottom:0">Tactics and habits that separate informed investors from the noise.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="tips-grid">
    <div class="tip-card">
      <div class="tip-tag">Research</div>
      <span class="tip-icon">📊</span>
      <h3>Read Earnings Reports</h3>
      <p>Before analysts spin the narrative, read the raw 10-Q and 10-K filings yourself. The real story is in the footnotes — look for changes in revenue recognition, debt structure, and forward guidance.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-card">
      <div class="tip-tag">Macro</div>
      <span class="tip-icon">🏦</span>
      <h3>Track the Fed</h3>
      <p>Interest rate decisions ripple through every asset class. When rates rise, bonds fall, growth stocks compress, and cash becomes competitive. Understanding this cycle gives you a macro edge.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-card">
      <div class="tip-tag">Psychology</div>
      <span class="tip-icon">🧠</span>
      <h3>Control Your Emotions</h3>
      <p>Fear and greed drive markets short-term. The investors who outperform buy when others panic and sit still when others chase. Build a rules-based system and stick to it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-card">
      <div class="tip-tag">Timing</div>
      <span class="tip-icon">📅</span>
      <h3>Understand Seasonality</h3>
      <p>Markets have predictable seasonal patterns — "Sell in May," the Santa Claus rally, earnings season volatility. They aren't guarantees, but knowing them adds context to your decisions.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-card">
      <div class="tip-tag">Intelligence</div>
      <span class="tip-icon">🔍</span>
      <h3>Follow Institutional Money</h3>
      <p>Large funds move markets. Track 13F filings to see what hedge funds and institutional investors are buying. When smart money concentrates in a sector, pay attention.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-card">
      <div class="tip-tag">Risk</div>
      <span class="tip-icon">🛡️</span>
      <h3>Hedge Your Positions</h3>
      <p>Options, inverse ETFs, and asset class diversification can protect your portfolio during downturns. You don't need to avoid risk — you need to manage it intelligently.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-card">
      <div class="tip-tag">Strategy</div>
      <span class="tip-icon">⚡</span>
      <h3>Rebalance Regularly</h3>
      <p>As positions grow, your portfolio drifts from your target allocation. Rebalancing quarterly locks in gains from winners and systematically buys into laggards — a disciplined form of buy low, sell high.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-card">
      <div class="tip-tag">Tax</div>
      <span class="tip-icon">💡</span>
      <h3>Tax-Loss Harvesting</h3>
      <p>Sell losing positions to offset taxable gains, then immediately buy a similar (not identical) asset. This lowers your tax bill without changing your market exposure. A free return boost most investors ignore.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

